  "notes_sections": [
    "There is more than one definition of sign in common use for complex numbers.  The definition used here, :math:`x/|x|`, is the more common and useful one, but is different from the one used in numpy prior to version 2.0, :math:`x/\\sqrt{x*x}`, which is equivalent to ``sign(x.real) + 0j if x.real != 0 else sign(x.imag) + 0j``."
  ],
